<p>
<seg id=1> The international supervising personnels entered and stationed in Kosovo still had hopes of resuming the ceasefire, even though there had been fighting between the Selvian security troops and Albanian separatists for several days continuously. </seg>
<seg id=2> A spokesman of the supervising personnels announced on Monday in Pristina that the situation of Kosovo Province in Yugslavia was calm at present. </seg>
<seg id=3> During last week's fighting, at least 12 people died. </seg>
<seg id=4> Galmeke, a Pole, Chairman of the European Safety and Cooperation Organization condemned this violent conflict caused by the two sides involved. </seg>
